In Python you can read data from every files by function 'open()'
In Python you can close every file what file you had opened before by methons 'close()'
In Python you can read word at all by methons 'read()'.Methons 'read()' will give you a long string.
In Python you can cross absolute path and relative path to help Python find file that you want to use.
In Python you can read data a line of by methons 'readlines'.
In Python you can create list including every list in file by assignment
In Python you can find whether there are data you miss by keyword 'in'
